Rating: 0
Don't let concerns about salmonella deter you from trying this recipe or the one made famous by Joe's Stone Crab (my favorite of the two). For the paranoid among us, here's a tested workaround: 1. Beat the egg yolks 2. Stir the sweetened condensed milk and the lime juice into the yolks 3. Heat the mixture over hot, not boiling, water, stirring constantly, until mixture reaches 160°F on an instant-read thermometer. 4. Remove from heat, stir in lime zest, pour filling into prepared crust, and proceed with baking instructions (since eggs are already heated when they go into the oven, you may want to reduce baking time by a minute or two). Optionally, if not traditionally, the crust for Joe's pie can be made with half the sugar called for in the recipe, as the filling is very sweet. And I heartily concur with those who feel that a topping of whipped cream - not meringue - is the way to go!

