Rating: 2
Some people have expressed concern about the use of raw eggs in the recipe. Fear not, the acid content of the lime juice is enough to effectively 'cook' the eggs. As long as the pie is allow to chill in the fridge before serving (I would make it at least a few hours ahead), you do not need to cook it at all. Skip the topping and add whipped cream. Whipped cream, or nothing at all, would be the traditional topping. Before making this recipe you should be aware that Key Limes are very different from regular limes. Key Limes are very tart and their juice is a pale yellow, not green. Although a regular lime pie would probably be tasty, lemons would make a better substitution if you cannot find Key Limes. Remember: If it's green, it's not a REAL Key lime pie!

Rating: 0
