I'm afraid I wouldn't try this recipe due to the samonella bacteria that raw eggs present. And I doubt that the baking of the merangue would sufficiently cook the egg enough. I would be extremely careful with using raw eggs in any recipe, particularly if feeding it to young children, pregnant women or those with weakened immune systems. I would like to find out more about pasturized eggs as mentioned by a fellow reviewer.

